  "texts": [
    "• Foraminifera: Single-celled protists with calcareous shells, Foraminifera are among the most studied microfossils.",
    "They are found in both benthic and planktonic forms, and have a diverse range of shell shapes.",
    "They are widely used for correlating and dating marine sedimentary deposits, and understanding past marine environments (Palmer and Elderfield 1985).",
    "Their shells are often preserved as calcite, a form of calcium carbonate.",
    "• Ostracods: small crustaceans with a calcified exoskeleton."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "They are widely used for correlating and dating marine sedimentary deposits, and understanding past marine environments (Palmer and Elderfield 1985)."
  ]
}